node.text:
What is diaphragmatic breathing? With my friend @missnikkileigh (full episode of Scan My Brain with Nikki out this Saturday stay tuned!)

Diaphragmatic breathing is intended to help you use the diaphragm correctly while breathing to:

Strengthen the diaphragm
Decrease the work of breathing by slowing your breathing rate
Decrease oxygen demand
Use less effort and energy to breathe
Diaphragmatic breathing technique

Lie on your back on a flat surface or in bed, with your knees bent and your head supported. You can use a pillow under your knees to support your legs. Place one hand on your upper chest and the other just below your rib cage. This will allow you to feel your diaphragm move as you breathe.

node.text: Today on Scan My Brain, we welcome the host of one of my favorite podcasts The School of Greatness and entrepreneur @lewishowes into @amen_clinics. We discuss Lewis' trauma growing up as well as not functioning at the level he felt he was capable to. We also discuss his football career and see what damage was caused to his brain because of it. Look inside his brain scan to see what we found. #brainhealth #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness

node.text: My team shared this tweet with me "Simone Biles probably won't hear your tweets about her "quitting" or "playing the mental health card" but your friends who struggle with mental health issues will. So important. Mental health does not discriminate and can be hugely impactful in someone's life even if they are a Olympian. Everyone is fighting a hard battle, be kind be thoughtful. What is diaphragmatic breathing? With my friend @missnikkileigh (full episode of Scan My Brain with Nikki out this Saturday stay tuned!)

Diaphragmatic breathing is intended to help you use the diaphragm correctly while breathing to:

Strengthen the diaphragm
Decrease the work of breathing by slowing your breathing rate
Decrease oxygen demand
Use less effort and energy to breathe
Diaphragmatic breathing technique

Lie on your back on a flat surface or in bed, with your knees bent and your head supported. You can use a pillow under your knees to support your legs. Place one hand on your upper chest and the other just below your rib cage. This will allow you to feel your diaphragm move as you breathe.

Let's discuss self-care.

When my patients and I discuss what it means to take care of yourself, it is often around managing your thoughts, mind and taking care of areas of your life that are deficit. Creating boundaries within yourself is a great place to start with self-care. Block out 45 minutes of the day to do something you love (15 minutes reading, 30 exercising) whatever it is. Start little. You deserve it.

node.text: Simone Biles withdraws from the women's team gymnastic final on Tuesday as the Russia Olympic Committee (ROC) took gold at the Tokyo 2020 Olympics.
